SIMPLE: mishap
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mishap
<hw>Mis*hap"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Evil accident; ill
luck; misfortune; mischance.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Secure from worldly chances and <qex>mishaps</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mishap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mishap
<hw>Mis*hap"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To happen
unluckily; -- used impersonally.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧If
that me <xex>mishap</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mishappen</ent>⟦br⟧
